I've been screwed by my airline so much the past couple of hours, I am considering just writing a story about some traveler who gets stuck at the airport and eaten by some anthro plane-gon, in an attempt to work out this trauma.

And yes, I am serious.
I swear, I just went through all the stages of the "Mr. Incredible Turns Uncanny" meme and then got to the "Canny" part where the Doom Eternal song is playing.

Seriously, the airline was like "Yeah uh, we overbooked your flight, but there's still room for the one you initially had, you want that?"

Me: "YES, JUST GET ME THERE TONIGHT, I DON'T CARE"

Me: "oh yeah, give me a window seat too, plz"

OKAY JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE WITH THE AIRLINE, I I'M ABLE TO MAKE IT TO TFF TONIGHT , BUT NOW I'M BACK ON TO ARRIVING AT 12:30AM.

HOLY HELL, I AM EXCITED AND ALSO LIKE "WHY IS THE AIRLINE DICKING WITH ME SO MUCH"

Whatever, I'm just glad to be there tonight . Who tf needs sleep? https://t.co/MwVM8xBRj9

*As the sergal lifted his paw, you came with it, caught in the pillowy-like pad of his sole, as he carried you along through the fields of Japan*

"A strange request, but it fills my heart with joy knowing one would like my feet so much. I wonder if I can find others like them?"

*Slowly, he presses his paw down onto you. The immense weight knocks you onto your back, your view of the world replaced by dark sergal pawpad, as you feel your body sink into the soft flesh.*

*So soft, that...it didn't hurt at all. Only one issue, you were now stuck underfoot*

*The sergal stands up once again, looming over you, as he raises his foot just over your head, splaying his large toes. The scent of freshly fallen autumn leaves filled the air, his natural scent rather pleasing, tufts of crimson fur lined the back of his paw*

*The sergal cocks his head in confusion, puzzled by your request*

"W-wont that hurt you? I don't want to...are you sure?"
"Well, it seems to make you happy. And if it pleases you, then it shall please me as well. Please brace yourself little one, my pads may be soft, but..."

*Each word causes the uvula in the back of his throat to sway, his tonsils glistening with saliva, before his lips form a smile on the sergal's wedge-like face*

"I don't wish to harm anyone, however. I just travel from place to-come again?"

"Y-you want me to step on you?"

"My name is Akiyoshi. I used to be of a similar height as yourself, but...it seems I've been cursed to grow as tall as the sky itself."

*as he speaks, his dark lips part, revealing a tapered pink tongue, the ridged sergal tongue widening towards the back of his throat*

*The sergal ronin kneels in front of you, his head topped off with a large brimmed straw Sandogasa hat, his yellow eyes peeking out from underneath*

"My apologies, little one. I didn't mean to almost step on you...it is difficult to see small ones such as yourself from so high."

*The sergal suddenly looks down, noticing you, letting out a gasp, before he steps down beside you, the foot causing the ground to quake beside you*

"Oh dear, not again. I almost stepped on a poor, little creature...I really must get better at this whole 'being big' thing..."

*as he stomps through the fields, he strides over towards you. A digitgrade foot raises high over you, casting a shadow, the black pad covered in grass and a variety of farm plants, the paw like an eclipse blocking out the sunlight*

*The giant sergal ronin, towering over the tallest pagodas of Sengoku-Era Japan, ponders to himself, unknowingly flattening the farmlands surrounding the area underneath his massive, prehensile, fully-padded feetpaws*

"Hmmm...'tis such a bother, having grown so large."

Even with everything going on in the world, I'm happy to be here, surrounded by wonderful people and knowing that I can push myself ahead now.

No matter what comes, I will forge ahead. Together, with you.

Happy new year!

4/4

I've forged stronger bonds with folks I've known for a long time and created new ones with wonderful friends. I've gotten back into writing hard, and I've worked on casting away a lot of personal doubt and shame for myself. I never realized I could feel this happy in my life

3/?

I honestly almost didn't make it this year. A lot happened, with being forced to move multiple times, changing jobs, financial issues and personal stress. I...was very scared at one point.

But I chose to continue. And...I'm so thankful I did.

2/?
